  <div class="main">
      <h1>Dragon Boat Festival:</h1>
      <p>The Dragon Boat Festival, also known as the Duanyang Festival, Dragon Boat Festival, Chongwu Festival, Dragon Festival, Zhengyang Festival, Tianzhong Festival, etc. The festival takes place on the fifth day of the fifth lunar month and is a traditional Chinese folk festival. The Dragon Boat Festival originated from the celestial worship. From the midsummer Dragon Boat Festival, Canglong Qisu flew to Zhengnan Zhongtian, which is the day of Long Feitian, that is, the fifth line of "The Book of Changes · Qian Gua" said: "Flying dragon is in the sky." The origin of the Dragon Boat Festival covers the contents of ancient astrological culture, humanistic philosophy, etc., and contains profound and rich cultural connotations; it is mixed in the inheritance and development; the Dragon Star on the Dragon Boat Festival is both "getting" and "getting right". Like. The Dragon Boat Festival and the Rice Dumplings are the two major customs of the Dragon Boat Festival. The traditions have been passed down from ancient times in China and have not stopped until now.
The Dragon Boat Festival was originally a feast of the Dragon Ancestors founded by the ancestors of Wuyue in the South. According to legend, Chu Yuan poet Qu Yuan jumped to the Luo River on May 5 to kill himself. Later, people also regarded the Dragon Boat Festival as a festival to commemorate Qu Yuan; in general, the Dragon Boat Festival originated from the ancient Chinese people's choice of "Dragon Ascension" Jiri Festival Long Zu, infused with the summer season "relief and epidemic prevention" fashion, regards the Dragon Boat Festival as "evil" and "evil day" from the northern Central Plains, with the commemoration of historical figures such as Qu Yuan. The formation of the Dragon Boat Festival customs can be said to be the product of the integration of North and South customs.
The Dragon Boat Festival culture has a wide influence in the world, and some countries and regions in the world also celebrate the Dragon Boat Festival. In May 2006, the State Council placed it first. The Dragon Boat Festival and the Spring Festival, the Ching Ming Festival, and the Mid-Autumn Festival are also called the four traditional Chinese festivals. Approved the national intangible cultural heritage list; since 2008, it has been listed as a national legal holiday. In September 2009, the United Nations formally approved its inclusion in the "List of Representative Works of Human Intangible Cultural Heritage", and the Dragon Boat Festival became China's first selected non-legacy festival in the world.</p>
